# ${name}

> ${description}

This is a **standalone Foundry Hosted Agent** exported from a Kratos
use-case. It's a self-contained clone of Kratos's hosted-agent runtime,
trimmed down to a single persona (`${use_case}`).

## What's in the ZIP

```
${slug}-agent/
├── azure.yaml                # azd config — one hosted-agent service
├── src/
│   ├── hosted-agent/         # The Kratos hosted-agent runtime (verbatim)
│   │   ├── main.py           # Copilot SDK + InvocationAgentServerHost
│   │   ├── Dockerfile        # Builds the agent container image
│   │   ├── agent.yaml        # Container-side agent descriptor
│   │   ├── agent.manifest.yaml
│   │   └── pyproject.toml
│   └── backend/app/          # Kratos backend modules (CopilotAgent, SkillRegistry…)
├── use-cases/${use_case}/    # ONLY the chosen persona
├── mocks/                    # Bundled stdio MCP mock servers
└── infra/                    # Bicep — AI Foundry + Cosmos + Search + Blob + KV + ACR
    ├── main.bicep
    ├── main.parameters.json
    └── modules/
```

Because the runtime is identical to Kratos's, the exported agent behaves
**exactly** like the `${name}` persona did in Kratos — same `CopilotAgent`,
same `SkillRegistry`, same event types, same APM lazy-loading, same
Cosmos persistence.

## Prerequisites

- [Azure Developer CLI (azd)](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/developer/azure-developer-cli/install-azd) — installed and logged in
- [Azure CLI (az)](https://learn.microsoft.com/cli/azure/install-azure-cli) — installed and logged in
- An Azure subscription with quota for AI Foundry + Cosmos DB + AI Search
- The `azd ai agents` extension:
  ```bash
  azd extension install azure.ai.agents
  ```

## Deploy

```bash
azd auth login
azd init                            # picks env name + subscription
azd env set AZURE_LOCATION eastus2  # or your preferred region
azd up
```

`azd up`:
1. **Provisions** the AI Foundry account/project, Cosmos DB, AI Search,
   Blob Storage, Key Vault, App Insights, ACR + role assignments
2. **Builds** the agent container via ACR remoteBuild
3. **Registers** the hosted agent on the Foundry project via the
   `azure.ai.agents` extension
4. **Runs the post-deploy RBAC hook** (`hooks/postdeploy.sh` on Linux/macOS,
   `hooks/postdeploy.ps1` on Windows — azd picks the right one) to grant the
   data-plane roles (`AcrPull`, `Cognitive Services OpenAI User`,
   `Cognitive Services User`, `Foundry User`) to the hosted-agent's instance +
   blueprint managed identities. These identities are created by Foundry
   **after** Bicep provisioning, so they can't be granted via Bicep — the hook
   discovers them via `azd ai agent show` and runs `az role assignment create`.
5. **Prints** an Agent Playground URL

> **Note:** If the first invocation reports `agent_version_failed` with
> "Failed to pull container image", the AcrPull grant landed after Foundry
> tried to pull the image. Re-run `azd deploy` to publish a new version —
> Foundry will retry the pull with the grant in place.

After deploy completes:
* Open the Playground URL and chat with the agent
* Or hit the `/invocations` endpoint directly with `POST` + JSON body

## Local development

The same runtime can be started outside Azure for fast iteration:

```bash
cp .env.template .env             # fill in MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME etc.
cd src/hosted-agent
uv sync --prerelease=allow
uv run python main.py             # → http://localhost:8088/invocations
```

For BYOK Foundry, set `FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT` and `MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME`
in `.env` and `az login` — `DefaultAzureCredential` does the rest.

## Project structure

| Path                              | Purpose                                                              |
|-----------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `src/hosted-agent/main.py`        | Single-tenant entry point (`InvocationAgentServerHost` on port 8088) |
| `src/backend/app/services/`       | `CopilotAgent`, `SkillRegistry`, `CosmosService`, `ApmService`, …    |
| `use-cases/${use_case}/`          | The persona: `SYSTEM_PROMPT.md`, `skills/`, `.mcp.json`, `apm.yml`    |
| `mocks/packages/`                 | npm-installed stdio MCP mock servers                                  |
| `infra/main.bicep`                | Trimmed Kratos infra — drops Container App backend, APIM, Static Web |

## Customizing the persona

Edit `use-cases/${use_case}/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md` (system prompt) or any
`skills/<name>/SKILL.md` file, then `azd deploy` to push the change. The
hosted agent's `SkillRegistry` reloads from disk on every cold start; the
seeded blob storage is kept in sync via `seed_from_local()`.

